.IX Title "GIT-COMMENT 1"
.TH GIT-COMMENT 1 "2015-06-10" "1.0.0.0" "Git Comment Manual"
.\" For nroff, turn off justification.  Always turn off hyphenation; it makes
.\" way too many mistakes in technical documents.
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH "NAME"
.Vb 1
\&    git\-comment \- Annotate git commits
.Ve
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 5
\&    git comment [\-m <msg>] [\-\-amend <comment>] [<commit>] [<filepath:line>]
\&    git comment \-\-delete <comment>
\&    git comment \-\-configure\-remote <remote>
\&    git comment \-\-help
\&    git comment \-v
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
git-comment adds, removes, or amends comments attached to git commits, without changing the commits themselves.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\-\-amend <comment>" 4
.IX Item "--amend <comment>"
Edit an existing comment. No modifications are made if a commit is specified but no comment with a given \s-1ID\s0 attached to the given commit.
.IP "\fI\-d\fR <comment>" 4
.IX Item "-d <comment>"
Remove a comment
.IP "\fI\-h\fR" 4
.IX Item "-h"
Gives a pretty-printed usage of the command
.IP "\fI\-m\fR <msg>, \-\-message=<msg>" 4
.IX Item "-m <msg>, --message=<msg>"
Use the provided message instead of prompting for message content
.IP "\fI\-v\fR, \-\-version" 4
.IX Item "-v, --version"
Print the current version number
.IP "\-\-configure\-remote" 4
.IX Item "--configure-remote"
Update the remote configuration to fetch and push comment changes by default
.IP "<commit>" 4
.IX Item "<commit>"
A commit
.IP "<filepath:line>" 4
.IX Item "<filepath:line>"
A reference to a file and line number, to make the annotation more specific
.IP "<remote>" 4
.IX Item "<remote>"
A remote name
.SH "ENVIRONMENT AND CONFIGURATION"
.IX Header "ENVIRONMENT AND CONFIGURATION"
git-comment uses the same editor, author, and pager settings as git. See
\&\fIgit-var\fR(1) for more details.
.SH "HOOKS"
.IX Header "HOOKS"
This command can run pre-comment and post-comment hooks.
.SH "DISCUSSION"
.IX Header "DISCUSSION"
Comment objects are blobs containing extra information about a commit and optionally a changed line within a the commit.
